# PERFORMANCE RULES

> Performance is a feature. Slow app = bad UX.

---

## TARGET METRICS

### Web Vitals
| Metric | Target | Description |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| **LCP** | < 2.5s | Largest Contentful Paint |
| **INP** | < 200ms | Interaction to Next Paint |
| **CLS** | < 0.1 | Cumulative Layout Shift |

---

## IMAGES

- Always use `next/image`
- `priority` for above-the-fold / LCP images
- `loading="lazy"` for below-the-fold
- `sizes` attribute for responsive
- Formats: WebP/AVIF (configured in next.config.ts)
- ❌ Never use plain `<img>` tags

---

## BUNDLE OPTIMIZATION

- Dynamic imports for heavy components (`next/dynamic`)
- Import only what you need (tree shaking)
- `optimizePackageImports` for large packages (lucide-react)
- Avoid importing entire libraries (`import _ from 'lodash'`)

---

## REACT OPTIMIZATION

- `React.memo` for list item components
- `useMemo` for expensive calculations only
- `useCallback` for stable function references passed as props
- ❌ Don't memoize simple derivations
- Virtualization for long lists (100+ items)

---

## CACHING

- HTTP Cache-Control headers for API routes (already configured)
- `next/image` caching (1 year TTL configured)
- Parallel queries with `Promise.all` when independent
- DB indexes for frequent queries

---

## DATABASE

- Select only needed fields
- Use `include` to avoid N+1
- Always paginate lists
- Use indexes for filtered/sorted columns

